(40, 19, 13, 1, 48, 9, 20, 'put his hands on them', 'Blessing of Children', 'Both passages emphasize the act of blessing children. In Matthew, Jesus is approached to bless little children, while in Genesis, Israel blesses Joseph''s sons. This connection highlights the importance of blessing the next generation.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 19, 14, 40, 18, 3, 3, 'little children', 'Children and the Kingdom of Heaven', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of being like little children to enter the kingdom of heaven. Matthew 19:14 highlights that children should come to Jesus, while Matthew 18:3 states that one must become like them to enter the kingdom.', 'theme', 0.46099999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
